            <td class="textheader">Corporate Investments planning</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="bodytext">Our Corporate Advisory  Bouquet of services includes advice on Corporate Treasury and investments of  PF/Gratuity Trusts and Superannuation Funds. We also provide investment banking  services for our corporate clients. Our unique <strong>Corporate Help Desk</strong> model helps your employees also on investment  &amp; Tax Planning related issues.<br />
              <br />
BFC Capital has built  its reputation in the field of Corporate Investment Planning, allied to high  professional standards. Being a Corporate/Institution, you must choose the right  investments for your organization, understand its financial implications, and  validate its returns. You can't afford an investment planning process that's  ad-hoc, cumbersome, or inaccurate. Unfortunately, current Corporate Financial Planning  tools face exactly these challenges, leading to a process that:
<ul type="disc">
  <li>Lacks consistency and scalability</li>
  <li>Relies on manual processes that lead to inaccuracies</li>
  <li>Offers limited analytical capabilities</li>
  <li>Makes rebalancing difficult </li>
</ul>
<strong>The Solution: A Consistent, Rigorous Planning Process-</strong>Track  investments&rsquo; performance with real-time analysis. We provide different  analytical tools, reports &amp; analysis, industry data, performance reports, that  enables you to improve the accuracy of the financial planning processes. &nbsp;<br />
<br />
We as an Independent Financial Adviser do not have tie-ups with any single  product provider; in fact we have a range of financial products available with  us &amp; have association with a no. of product providers. Therefore we can provide  the product or service truly meeting client&rsquo;s needs.&nbsp; The financial market  keeps on &nbsp;changing at a very fast pace,  therefore it is vital to review your investments and portfolio regularly. Our  services are tailored towards clients, who wish to develop an ongoing  relationship with their financial adviser, and therefore we offer a robust  review service to facilitate this. <br />
<br />
There are different types of investment  options available for investment planning viz: Money Market Instruments, Debt Securities,  Stocks Trading, Mutual Funds, Derivatives, Commodities, and Real Estate. One  needs to understand the importance of investments and the risk associated  therewith. One needs to be clear about the time horizon while selecting an 
                        Investment&nbsp;  product.<br clear="all" />
                        <br />
                        <strong>Need for Investment Management </strong><br clear="all" />
The need for Investment Management arrives at times of existence of large  number of complexities and instabilities of financial markets, and need for  sudden modification in the light of new regulatory issues. We as investment  managers are well versed in Financial Advisory and Wealth Management to serve our  clients. <br />
<br />
<br clear="all" />
<strong>Investment  Strategies </strong><br />
There are certain set of rules and behavioral procedures formulated in the  design guide supporting the investors in providing options on selection of the  investment assortment. Well planned investment strategies marks a great deal in  the investment decision making which is dependent on the period and the type of  investment option one opts for. </td>
